    {
      "id": "673b7f59dd2e76dfe17374a7ee66df53dd0e9c92",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-10-01 08:53:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\n(2 comments)\n\nI also wrote a similar patch http://review.whamcloud.com/12149 that I hadn't pushed until now.  It creates a temporary file in the directory and then uses:\n\n        lfs getstripe -M $file\n\nto determine the actual MDT that the file was created on.  That solves the problem of a potential default directory layout in the future, but doesn't solve the problem with test_mkdir() creating 2-stripe directories.  It probably makes sense to fix code using get_mds_idx() to use \"test_mkdir -c 1\" to avoid this problem.\n\nMy patch also does a bunch of other cleanups.  I'm not sure if it is better to actually create and delete a file for this test, or to use the FLDB method used in this patch.  If this one lands first, I can always rebase mine to use this method.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
